

---
const pageTitle = "Anima";
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <title>{pageTitle}</title>
    <style>
      :root {
        --paper: #ffffff;
        --ink: #000000;
        --line: #000000;
        --soft: #efefef;
        --blue: #0000ee;
        --red: #cc0000;
        --green: #008000;
      }

      html, body {
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
        background: var(--paper);
        color: var(--ink);
        font-family: "Times New Roman", Times, serif;
        font-size: 18px;
        line-height: 1.55;
      }

      a { text-decoration: underline; }
      a.blue { color: var(--blue); }
      a.red { color: var(--red); }
      a.green { color: var(--green); }

      .page {
        width: min(900px, calc(100% - 48px));
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 28px 0 60px;
      }

      .topbar {
        border: 1px solid var(--line);
        padding: 10px 14px;
        margin-bottom: 18px;
        text-align: center;
        background: #fafafa;
      }

      .topbar span {
        display: inline-block;
        margin: 0 8px;
        white-space: nowrap;
      }

      .frame {
        border: 1px solid var(--line);
        padding: 22px 24px 28px;
        position: relative;
        overflow: hidden;
        background:
          linear-gradient(to bottom, rgba(255,255,255,0.94), rgba(245,245,245,0.94)),
          repeating-linear-gradient(
            to bottom,
            rgba(0,0,0,0.018) 0px,
            rgba(0,0,0,0.018) 1px,
            transparent 1px,
            transparent 4px
          );
      }

      .symbol-bg {
        position: absolute;
        top: 50%;
        left: 50%;
        transform: translate(-50%, -50%) rotate(3deg);
        width: 300px;
        height: 300px;
        opacity: 0.2;
        pointer-events: none;
        user-select: none;
        z-index: 0;
      }

      .symbol-bg svg {
        width: 100%;
        height: 100%;
        display: block;
      }

      .content-layer {
        position: relative;
        z-index: 1;
      }

      h1 {
        font-size: 42px;
        text-align: center;
        margin: 0 0 8px;
        letter-spacing: 0.5px;
      }

      .subtitle {
        text-align: center;
        font-size: 15px;
        margin-bottom: 24px;
        text-transform: lowercase;
      }

      .divider {
        text-align: center;
        margin: 18px 0 24px;
      }

      p { margin: 0 0 16px; }

      .quote {
        margin: 22px auto;
        max-width: 680px;
        border: 1px solid var(--line);
        padding: 14px;
        background: linear-gradient(to bottom, #f3f3f3, #ebebeb);
        font-style: italic;
        text-align: center;
        box-shadow: inset 0 0 0 1px rgba(255,255,255,0.65);
      }

      .section-title {
        font-size: 28px;
        text-align: center;
        margin: 30px 0 14px;
      }

      .mini-links {
        text-align: center;
        margin-top: 30px;
      }

      .mini-links a {
        margin: 0 10px;
      }

      .footer-note {
        text-align: center;
        margin-top: 26px;
        font-size: 14px;
      }

      .content-layer p,
      .content-layer h1,
      .content-layer h2,
      .content-layer .subtitle,
      .content-layer .divider,
      .content-layer .quote,
      .content-layer .mini-links,
      .content-layer .footer-note {
        text-shadow: 0 0 1px rgba(255,255,255,0.45);
      }

      @media (max-width: 700px) {
        h1 { font-size: 34px; }
        .symbol-bg {
          width: 210px;
          height: 210px;
        }
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="page">
      <div class="topbar">
        <span>[ <a class="blue" href="/">home</a> ]</span>
        <span>[ <a class="blue" href="/archetypes/">archetypes index</a> ]</span>
        <span>[ <a class="green" href="/archetypes/shadow-archetype">previous</a> ]</span>
        <span>[ <a class="red" href="/archetypes/animus">next</a> ]</span>
      </div>

      <main class="frame">
        <div class="symbol-bg" aria-hidden="true">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 300 300" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none">
            <g stroke="#000000" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
              <path d="M20 160 C60 120, 100 200, 140 160 C180 120, 220 200, 260 160" />
              <path d="M20 190 C60 150, 100 230, 140 190 C180 150, 220 230, 260 190" />
              <path d="M20 130 C60 90, 100 170, 140 130 C180 90, 220 170, 260 130" />
              <circle cx="150" cy="150" r="90" />
            </g>
          </svg>
        </div>

        <div class="content-layer">
          <h1>Anima</h1>
          <p class="subtitle">archetypes / inner image / feeling / archive entry 003</p>

          <div class="divider">***</div>

          <p>
            The anima represents the inner feminine image within the psyche.
            It is not simply a gendered idea, but a pattern of feeling, image,
            receptivity, and emotional depth.
          </p>

          <p>
            It often appears in dreams, fantasies, and projections as a figure
            that draws attention inward. The anima can inspire creativity,
            relationship, and meaning, but can also distort perception if
            unconscious.
          </p>

          <div class="quote">
            the anima carries the image of what the ego does not fully know.
          </div>

          <h2 class="section-title">image and projection</h2>

          <p>
            The anima frequently appears projected onto others. A person may
            attribute depth, beauty, or mystery to someone, without realizing
            these qualities are partly arising from within.
          </p>

          <p>
            This projection can create strong attraction or emotional intensity.
            Over time, reality challenges the projection, leading to either
            disillusionment or deeper understanding.
          </p>

          <h2 class="section-title">relation to the self</h2>

          <p>
            As the anima becomes more conscious, it shifts from projection to
            relationship. Instead of being experienced only through others,
            it becomes a source of inner dialogue and feeling.
          </p>

          <p>
            This deepens the inner life and allows for a more balanced
            psychological structure.
          </p>

          <div class="mini-links">
            <a class="blue" href="/archetypes/">back to archetypes index</a>
            <a class="blue" href="/archetypes/animus">continue to: animus</a>
            <a class="red" href="/archetypes/shadow-archetype">shadow</a>
          </div>

          <p class="footer-note">
            this page is part of the hidden archive.
          </p>
        </div>
      </main>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>